Distribution. Specimens were collected in two areas characterized by different predominant water masses (
Fig. 1
). Some of them were found on the shelf and slope ( 133 to 1,007 m depth) of SW Iceland , off Faxafloi Bay to South of Vestmannaeyjar Island, in warmer waters ( 4.8 to 7.4 ºC). Most specimens were collected on the slope off NE Iceland , in Arctic colder, deeper waters (- 0.7 to - 0.8 ºC; 1,490 to 1,915 m ).
